ly try restarting your device.";i:12;s:47:"Videos you watch may be added to the TVs watch.";i:13;s:57:"Reasons Why Your Garage Door Keeps Opening After Closing.";i:14;s:96:"If your garage door keeps going back up after youve closed it the most common reason is because.";i:15;s:31:"The safety sensors are blocked.";i:16;s:59:"There are safety sensors at the bottom of your garage door.";i:17;s:67:"This infrared sensor passes a beam horizontally across the opening.";i:18;s:76:"Another common cause of garage doors acting this way is a faulty RPM sensor.";i:19;s:91:"Consult your owners manual or a trained garage door technician in replacing the RPM sensor.";i:20;s:74:"Parts can be purchased in online stores or directly from the manufacturer.";i:21;s:60:"If this has been helpful please click the green accept icon.";i:22;s:85:"If your garage door opens and suddenly stops it might be because of your logic board.";i:23;s:60:"The logic board receives and responds signals to any remote.";i:24;s:110:"You might need to consider replacing it if your door is not working properly or you may purchase a new opener.";i:25;s:15:"Answer 1 of 11.";i:26;s:39:"The most likely culprit is your sensor.";i:27;s:65:"It may be blocked off-track or the settings may be set too short.";i:28;s:78:"Here are the steps I recommend you follow to see if you can fix this yourself.";i:29;s:45:"These are summaries of an article found here.";i:30;s:40:"Your garage door sensor generally has t.";i:31;s:54:"If the lights stay on I recommend you check the gears.";i:32;s:53:"Replace the gears if there is any problems with them.";i:33;s:119:"Generally if there is a lot of plastic gear shaving inside the garage door opener the door spring needs to be adjusted.";i:34;s:48:"The plastic gears are designed to last 25 years.";i:35;s:18:"I hope this helps.";i:36;s:47:"To order garage door opener parts please visit.";i:37;s:184:"Limit switch malfunctions Similar to the travel setting the limit switch decides where the door